and 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB925B7FF61FA8082B9" authority="Perkins, 1981" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1981" box="[977,1293,151,176]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="piriferopsis">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB925B7FF61FBE182B9" box="[977,1132,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">S. piriferopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB92215FF6EFA8082B9" author="Perkins" box="[1139,1293,151,176]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1981) Syllidae (Polychaeta), principally from Florida, with descriptions of a new genus and twenty-one new species. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 93 (4), 1080 - 1172." type="journal article" year="1981">Perkins, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are the most similar species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB92707FF44FE5182DD" box="[353,476,189,212]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="monicae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92707FF44FEE282DD" box="[353,367,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB9271BFF44FE5182DD" box="[381,476,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">monicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92785FF45FDB082DC" bold="true" box="[483,573,188,213]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A223578A2B76FFB92785FF45FDB082DC" box="[483,573,188,213]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
due to the absence of parapodial glands. However, all these species have the body dorsally covered by papillae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB92444FF19FD6282F1" author="San" box="[546,751,224,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="San Martin, G. (1984 a) Descripcion de una nueva especie y revision del genero Sphaerosyllis (Polychaeta: Syllidae). Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 25, 375 - 391." type="journal article" year="1984" yearSuffix="a">San Martín 1984a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB9249CFF19FCBB82F1" author="San" box="[762,822,224,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Annelida Polychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Lol. 21. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 544." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB925CAFF19FBAA82F1" box="[940,1063,224,248]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="monicae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB925CAFF19FC3782FE" box="[940,954,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB925AEFF18FBAA82F1" box="[968,1063,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">monicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92248FF26FB0A82F1" bold="true" box="[1070,1159,223,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A223578A2B76FFB92248FF26FB0A82F1" box="[1070,1159,223,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the dorsal surface of the body is completely smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B76FFB926A8FEDEFDD983A5" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB926A8FEDEFDF48349" authority="Southern, 1914" authorityName="Southern" authorityYear="1914" box="[206,633,295,320]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bulbosa">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB926A8FEDEFE498349" box="[206,452,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sphaerosyllis bulbosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB927ADFEDEFDF48349" author="Southern" box="[459,633,295,320]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Southern, R. (1914) Clare Island Survey. Archiannelida and Polychaeta. Proceedings of the Royal Irish Academy, 31 (47), 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1914">Southern, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB92522FEDEFBCD8349" box="[836,1088,295,320]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="monicae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92522FEDEFBCD8349" box="[836,1088,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sphaerosyllis monicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92221FEDEFB2D8349" bold="true" box="[1095,1184,295,320]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A223578A2B76FFB92221FEDEFB2D8349" box="[1095,1184,295,320]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
regarding the absence of dorsal papillae. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB9278CFEB4FDEF836C" box="[490,610,332,357]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bulbosa">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB9278CFEB4FE75836D" box="[490,504,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB9246FFEB5FDEF836C" box="[521,610,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">bulbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents much shorter falciger blades (up to 10 µm long), secondarily simple chaetae on midbody, apparently by the loss of blades and enlargement of shafts, and aciculae straight, subdistally enlarged (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB927E0FE6DFDC483A5" author="San" box="[390,585,404,428]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Annelida Polychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Lol. 21. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 544." type="journal article" year="2003">San Martín 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B76FFB926A1FE4EFE9F8011" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Although we only have one specimen, we prefer to describe it as a new species, given the unusual and unique set of characters it presents, and the difficulties in collecting more material from the locality where the specimen was found.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65682B76FFB926A1FDDDFE608069" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B76FFB926A1FDDDFE608069" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB926A1FDDDFC9E8034" bold="true" box="[199,787,548,573]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Geographic distribution and bathymetric range.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB9257AFDDDFB968035" box="[796,1051,548,573]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="monicae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB9257AFDDDFB968035" box="[796,1051,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Sphaerosyllis monicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92243FDDDFB0C8034" bold="true" box="[1061,1153,548,573]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A223578A2B76FFB92243FDDDFB0C8034" box="[1061,1153,548,573]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is only known from the Campos Basin, at 
<quantity id="4C9C9B062B76FFB92705FDB1FE278056" box="[355,426,584,608]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.22" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" unit="m" value="722.0">722 m</quantity>
deep.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65682B76FFB926A1FD95FD1480A1" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B76FFB926A1FD95FD1480A1" blockId="18.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB926A1FD95FEC3808C" bold="true" box="[199,334,620,645]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is dedicated to Mônica Petti, a great Brazilian polychaetologist, for her relevant contribution to the knowledge of polychaetes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
